(thirdQuint)A Study of the Effects of Renal Impairment on the Pharmacokinetics and Tolerability of Eliglustat Tartrate.

 The total study duration from screening period is approximately 31 days.

 In stage 1, only subjects with severe renal impairment and normal renal function will be enrolled.

 Subjects with mild and moderate renal impairment may be enrolled in stage 2 if the results in subjects with severe renal impairment show a substantial effect of reduced renal function on pharmacokinetics.

